Title: Danfoss RA-FN 15 vertical angled valve 1/2"
Description: Made from brass with a smart nickel-plated finish, the Danfoss RA-FN radiator valve incorporates R 1/2" x Rp 1/2" connections, a chromium steel pressure pin and lifetime lubricated O-ring seal. Designed for use in two-pipe heating systems, the complete gland assembly is easily replaced with no need to drain down the system. It is supplied with a grey protective cap, used for manual regulation during the construction phase. This cap should not be used as a manual shut-off device.

Title: Danfoss RA-G20 angled valve 3/4"
Description: Designed for conventional one-pipe heating systems with thermosiphon operation, the Danfoss RA-G radiator valve is a high-capacity, low-resistance valve with large diameter valve cones for high capacities at low proportional offsets. This ensures that comfortable temperatures are maintained under all load conditions. This valve incorporates a gland-seal assembly that can be replaced without specialised tools and with no requirement to drain down. Connections are R 3/4" x Rp 3/4".
